msContents.summary: Persian translation and commentary of selections from Nahj al-balāghah. Arabic source-text is overlined and written in a different style to distinguish it.

author.persName: Rawghanī, Muḥammad Ṣāliḥ ibn Muḥammad Bāqir, -1632 or 1633
روغنى، محمد صالح بن محمد باقر، -
Sharīf al-Raḍī, Muḥammad ibn al-Ḥusayn, 969 or 970-1016
Sharīf al-Raḍī, Muḥammad ibn al-Ḥusayn, 969 or 970-1016

supportDesc.extent: 126 leaves : 220 x 125 (165 x 75) mm, bound to 225 x 125 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Persian in nastaʻliq; Arabic in naskh.

decoDesc.decoNote: Headpiece in blue and gold (f. 1v) with text on cloudbands in the first opening (f. 1v-2r) with gold, black, red and blue border-rules. Textblock on all other pages is border-ruled in black, gold, blue. Arabic source-text is overlined in gold and written in naskh to distinguish it from the translation. Gold, floriated tailpiece (f. 126r).

binding.p: Bound in brown leather with central mandorla, two pendants on the vertical axis and cornerpieces all with paper onlay. Inside covers have lighter brown leather pastedowns with stamped frame.
